<subsection xml:id="subsec-net-of-a-pyramid">
    <title>Net of a Pyramid</title>

    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Work in groups.}</m>
            </p>

            <p>
                <term>What you need:</term> model of a pyramid and a pair of scissors or cutting tool.
            </p>

            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Examine a pyramid model like the one shown below.
                        </p>

                        <image width="50%">
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="pyramid1">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                % Define vertices of the square base
                                \coordinate (A) at (-2,-1);
                                \coordinate (B) at (0,-1);
                                \coordinate (C) at (1,0);  
                                \coordinate (D) at (-1,0);  
                            
                                % Define the apex of the pyramid
                                \coordinate (E) at (0,3);  % Center above the square base
                                
                                % Draw the square base
                                \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle;
                                
                                % Draw edges connecting the apex to the base
                                \draw[thick] (E) -- (A);
                                \draw[thick] (E) -- (B);
                                \draw[thick] (E) -- (C);
                                \draw[style=dashed,thick] (E) -- (D);
                                
                                % Optional: Add shading for clarity with different blue shades
                                \fill[blue!20,opacity=0.5] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle;  % Base face
                                \fill[blue!40,opacity=0.5] (B) -- (C) -- (E) -- cycle; % Front face
                                \fill[blue!60,opacity=0.5] (D) -- (C) -- (E) -- cycle; % Right face
                                \fill[blue!80,opacity=0.5] (A) -- (D) -- (E) -- cycle; % Left face
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                            
                        </image>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Count and name the faces, edges, and vertices.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Carefully cut the pyramid along its edges.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Lay the pyramid flat after opening it up.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Observe the unfolded model and sketch its shape.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            What is the name of this 2D layout?
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Compare your drawing with those made by other groups. Do they look the same?
                        </p>
                    </li>

                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </activity>

    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
    </p>

    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    A square base pyramid has 5 faces. The base is a square and the other 4 faces are triangles.
                    A net of a square base pyramid is made up of 1 square and 4 triangles.             
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    A rectangle base pyramid has 5 faces. The base is a rectangle and the other 4 faces are triangles.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    A triangle-base pyramid has a triangle as its base.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    The net of a pyramid is a two-dimensional representation of the three-dimensional shape of the pyramid. 
                    It is made up of the faces of the pyramid laid out flat, so that you can see all of the sides at once. 
                    The net of a pyramid is useful for visualizing the shape of the pyramid and for calculating its surface area and volume.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
       
